3. Die] An old form of the gen. Virg. Geo. i. Libra die somnique pares ubi fecerit horas. This form is preserved by the MSS. in several places in Sallust, eg. ἄκρην. 52, 97, though here many read diei.

4. Plerumque noctis processit] Comp. Juyur. 51, multum diei processerat. Lucan, vii. 423, compares the advance of the Roman empire to the progress of a heavenly body through the sky: Te geminum Titan procedere vidit in axem.
